cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fine-grained visual classification and addresses the problem of inter-class similarity in FGVC datasets using a novel optimization procedure for neural network training. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a regularization technique to reduce overfitting in neural networks. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of AI models on FGVC tasks. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel optimization procedure for neural network training. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with visual classification tasks on multimedia datasets.
